	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actor" title="Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor">Best Actor in a Supporting Role</a> (Hugh Griffith)</li>
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress" title="Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress">Best Actress in a Supporting Role</a> (Diane Cilento)</li>
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress" title="Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress">Best Actress in a Supporting Role</a> (Dame Edith Evans)</li>
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress" title="Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress">Best Actress in a Supporting Role</a> (Joyce Redman)</li>
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Art_Direction" title="Academy Award for Best Art Direction">Best Art Direction-Set Decoration, Color</a> (<a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ralph_W._Brinton" title="Ralph W. Brinton">Ralph W. Brinton</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ted_Marshall" title="Ted Marshall">Ted Marshall</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jocelyn_Herbert" title="Jocelyn Herbert">Jocelyn Herbert</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josie_MacAvin" title="Josie MacAvin">Josie MacAvin</a>).</li>
      </ul>
      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i>Tom Jones</i> is the only film in the history of the Academy in which three actresses were nominated for Best Supporting Actress Oscar. All three nominations were unsuccessful, however, as the Academy Award in this category went to <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Margaret_Rutherford" title="Margaret Rutherford">Margaret Rutherford</a> for her role in <i><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_V.I.P.s" title="The V.I.P.s">The V.I.P.s</a></i>.</p>
